version: 1
display_name: VCFI-9X-000009 - The VMware Cloud Foundation Operations PostgreSQL service must initiate session auditing upon startup.
global_description: |-
  Session auditing is for use when a user's activities are under investigation. To be sure of capturing all activity during those periods when session auditing is in use, it needs to be in operation for the whole time the PostgreSQL is running.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFI-9X-000009
  srg:
    - SRG-APP-000092-DB-000208
  cci:
    - CCI-001464
  nist:
    - AU-14 (1)
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_operations_postgresql:
    type: custom
    desc: The VMware Cloud Foundation Operations PostgreSQL service must initiate session auditing upon startup.
    control_id: VCFI-9X-000009
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      As a database administrator, perform the following at the command prompt:

      # su - postgres -c "/opt/vmware/vpostgres/current/bin/psql -p 5433 -A -t -c 'SHOW log_destination;'"

      Example result:

      stderr

      If the "log_destination" setting is not configured to "stderr", this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Session auditing is for use when a user's activities are under investigation. To be sure of capturing all activity during those periods when session auditing is in use, it needs to be in operation for the whole time the PostgreSQL is running.
    remediation: |-
      As a database administrator, perform the following at the command prompt:

      # su - postgres -c "/opt/vmware/vpostgres/current/bin/psql -p 5433 -A -t -c \"ALTER SYSTEM SET log_destination = 'stderr';\""

      Reload the PostgreSQL service by running the following command:

      # systemctl restart vpostgres-repl.service
